	<h1>
    <a href="/" id="title"></a>
	</h1>
	</div>
<div id="md" style="display: none;">
<!-- markdown -->
$e^\theta = cos\theta + isin\theta$

$cos\theta$ is not linear. $e^\theta$ provides linear-like property.

etc.

$cos(\alpha+\beta)$ is difficult to extract. With the formula, we have 

$e^{\alpha+\beta} = cos(\alpha+\beta) + isin(\alpha+\beta)$

$e^{\alpha+\beta} = e^\alpha e^\beta = cos\alpha cos\beta - sin\alpha sin\beta + i(cos\alpha sin\beta + sin\alpha cos\beta)$

Two complex number is equal if and only if their real parts and imagine parts equal, respectively.

So we have

$cos(\alpha+\beta) = cos\alpha cos\beta - sin\alpha sin\beta$
$sin(\alpha+\beta) = cos\alpha sin\beta + sin\alpha cos\beta$

<!-- markdown end -->
</div>
