amily: MathJax_Main; padding-left: 0.202em;">+</span><span class="mi" id="MathJax-Span-1509" style="font-family: MathJax_Math-italic; padding-left: 0.202em;">i</span><span class="mo" id="MathJax-Span-1510" style="font-family: MathJax_Main;">(</span><span class="mi" id="MathJax-Span-1511" style="font-family: MathJax_Math-italic;">c</span><span class="mi" id="MathJax-Span-1512" style="font-family: MathJax_Math-italic;">o</span><span class="mi" id="MathJax-Span-1513" style="font-family: MathJax_Math-italic;">s</span><span class="mi" id="MathJax-Span-1514" style="font-family: MathJax_Math-italic;">α</span><span class="mi" id="MathJax-Span-1515" style="font-family: MathJax_Math-italic;">s</span><span class="mi" id="MathJax-Span-1516" style="font-family: MathJax_Math-italic;">i</span><span class="mi" id="MathJax-Span-1517" style="font-family: MathJax_Math-italic;">n</span><span class="mi" id="MathJax-Span-1518" style="font-family: MathJax_Math-italic;">β<span style="display: inline-block; overflow: hidden; height: 1px; width: 0.003em;"></span></span><span class="mo" id="MathJax-Span-1519" style="font-family: MathJax_Main; padding-left: 0.202em;">+</span><span class="mi" id="MathJax-Span-1520" style="font-family: MathJax_Math-italic; padding-left: 0.202em;">s</span><span class="mi" id="MathJax-Span-1521" style="font-family: MathJax_Math-italic;">i</span><span class="mi" id="MathJax-Span-1522" style="font-family: MathJax_Math-italic;">n</span><span class="mi" id="MathJax-Span-1523" style="font-family: MathJax_Math-italic;">α</span><span class="mi" id="MathJax-Span-1524" style="font-family: MathJax_Math-italic;">c</span><span class="mi" id="MathJax-Span-1525" style="font-family: MathJax_Math-italic;">o</span><span class="mi" id="MathJax-Span-1526" style="font-family: MathJax_Math-italic;">s</span><span class="mi" id="MathJax-Span-1527" style="font-family: MathJax_Math-italic;">β<span style="display: inline-block; overflow: hidden; height: 1px; width: 0.003em;"></span></span><span class="mo" id="MathJax-Span-1528" style="font-family: MathJax_Main;">)</span></span><span style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; height: 2.302em;"></span></span></span><span style="display: inline-block; overflow: hidden; vertical-align: -0.372em; border-left: 0px solid; width: 0px; height: 1.503em;"></span></span></nobr><span class="MJX_Assistive_MathML" role="presentation"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD"><mi>α</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>β</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mi>α</mi></msup><msup><mi>e</mi><mi>β</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>c</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>s</mi><mi>α</mi><mi>c</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>s</mi><mi>β</mi><mo>−</mo><mi>s</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>α</mi><mi>s</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>β</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>i</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>c</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>s</mi><mi>α</mi><mi>s</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>β</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>s</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>α</mi><mi>c</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>s</mi><mi>β</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math></span></span><script type="math/tex" id="MathJax-Element-78">e^{\alpha+\beta} = e^\alpha e^\beta = cos\alpha cos\beta - sin\alpha sin\beta + i(cos\alpha sin\beta + sin\alpha cos\beta)</script></p>

<p>Two complex number is equal if and only if their real parts and imagine parts equal, respectively.</p>

<p>So we have</p>

